        "link-href": "/fields/inline",
        "link-text": "Learn about inline fields",
        "content": {
            "header": [
                "Inline Fields"
            ],
            "section": [
                {
                    "type": "p",
                    "text": [
                        "Inline fields are the most basic type of content representation. Essentially these are HTML",
                        "tags that should only contain plain text and/or other inline fields."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "p",
                    "text": [
                        "<u>For example, we can have a whole sentence underlined with a few <i>words</i> also in <i>italics</i></u>.",
                        "Yet these are not considered to be Enjin Container Fields."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    },

    {
        "type": "content",
        "tag": "container-fields",
        "profile": "outer--inner",
        "padding": "both",
        "margins": "both",
        "jump-top": "true",
        "jump-link": "true",
        "link-href": "/fields/container",
        "link-text": "Learn about container fields",
        "content": {
            "header": [
                "Container Fields"
            ],
            "section": [
                {
                    "type": "p",
                    "text": [
                        "Container fields are like inline-fields except that they're allowed to have more variable",
                        "types of content within their HTML tags and typically aren't sources of content in-and-of",
                        "themselves. A good example are table fields while a murky example is the paragraph field."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    },

